what is a good inexpensive champagne for a wedding reception any helpful thoughts thanks if you are just looking for sparkling wine then there are many varieties on the market which you can get from under usd but note that these are not from the champagne region in france which supposedly reserves exclusive rights to the use of the name hence names like vins moussex spumante from italy cava from spain or sekt from germany or even the american versions however since its a wedding reception and ifyou feel you need to be particular and want to impress go look in your local online wine retailer for non vintage brut champagnes they are the cheapest and yet retains the exclusivity of the branding good luck The Cure 10cc Orange Order Les Savy Fav Placebo (band) Frankie Goes to Hollywood Battlefield 2 The Subtle Knife Sex show Bee Gees LOL (Internet slang) Billboard Hot 100 Friends Babes in Toyland (1934 film) Lol Coxhill Ghastly's Ghastly Comic Three Imaginary Boys Marguerite Duras Lady Godiva Sin City Palindrome The Damned The Beach Boys Nursery rhyme The Boondock Saints Hot Hot Heat 2channel Andy Bell (musician) Muslim ibn Aqeel Johnny Moss Avenue Q Can't Hardly Wait The Times They Are A-Changin' Ford GT40 LaToya Jackson Phoebe Buffay's songs Joe Hill The Freewheelin' Bob Dylan Charles Manson KISS (band) Pure Pwnage Fiddler on the Roof Hide and Seek (Stargate Atlantis) Chicken Samuel Goldwyn Hagbard and Signy Shania Twain Alcoholics Anonymous The Hoobs Jim Morrison Electric Light Orchestra From Genesis to Revelation Shake It Off Peeps Ocean's Twelve Max Beerbohm The Rasmus William Saroyan Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Mary Jane Kelly Battle of Thermopylae AFI (band) The Mexicools Incarnations of Immortality Shrek 2 Symposium Musical theater Methos Radio Yerevan Pac-Man Project Superstar Theobald Wolfe Tone Halaal Noah Trapped in the Closet Shaggy dog story Cocktail Carl Michael Bellman The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Social rule Godley & Creme Rama